    "created_at": "2015-06-08T16:24:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-08T16:24:18Z",
    "body": "I definitely agree that the design of liblibc needs to be re-thought, but I don't want to hastily go into a situation we're not prepared for. I think at this time we're not prepared for a sharding like @nagisa mentions, and I agree that this is leading towards that direction. \n\nThe alternative that I can think of is to continue the direction of liblibc being a \"this is the system's API interface\" kind of crate. There's definitely pros and cons in both directions, but it's something at least to consider.\n",
